---
title: Modals
---
p.-text Modals are windows used for displaying prompts and subtasks without losing context of the parent application.

h3 Examples
p.-text
  | Modals are composed of several parts. To render a modal, include a modal backdrop, modal header, modal body,
  | and modal footer (optional).

h4 Base
.example.-mb3
  .a-modal__backdrop.-p6(style="position:relative;border-top-left-radius:3px;border-top-right-radius:3px;")
    .a-modal(style="margin-top:0;")
      .a-modal__header
        h3.a-modal__title Modal Title
        button.a-modal__close
      .a-modal__content
        p.-text.-m0 Modal content
      .a-modal__footer
        button.a-btn Cancel
        button.a-btn.-brand.-ml2 Save
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-modal__backdrop">
      <div class="a-modal">
        <div class="a-modal__header">
          <h3 class="a-modal__title">Modal Title</h3>
          <button class="a-modal__close"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="a-modal__content">
          <p class="-text -m0">Modal content</p>
        </div>
        <div class="a-modal__footer">
          <button class="a-btn">Cancel</button>
          <button class="a-btn -brand -ml2">Save</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

